Description:
*The plumbing vent on the roof is not adequate height. The vent pipe is recommended to be no taller than 6 inches above the roof. I recommend further evaluation and correct as necessary
*Radon vent on the roof is too short - this can become a potential health issue if ever blocked by snow or other objects
*The water pressure was above the normal operating pressure. Anything above 80 PSI is potentially detrimental to the homes water supply lines and fixtures. It is recommended that the pressure regulator be adjusted, and lower the pressure to approximately 65-80 PSI which is adequate for almost all households. Water pressure was measured using a gauge at an exterior hose bib.
• Adjustment to the pressure reducing valve, located in the garage, is needed to bring the pressure in the home into the 40-80 PSI range as required by code. This is the second request for this repair.
*Some of the supply pipe insulation is incomplete in the crawlspace. Be sure all supply lines in unheated spaces have been adequately insulated to protect from freezing conditions that could damage the pipes and to prevent heat loss.

Description:
Invitation to the 2026 GRO Parade of Homes Builder Kickoff Event

Join us for an exciting afternoon as we officially kick off the 2026 GRO Parade of Homes! This annual event brings together the region’s top builders, developers, trades, and suppliers to launch planning for Clark County’s premier home showcase. The Builder Kickoff Event will be held Wednesday, October 29, 2025, from 1:00–3:00 p.m. at the BIA office. Enjoy refreshments, meet the 2026 Parade builders, and hear from the BIA team as we outline responsibilities, timelines, and resources that ensure another successful Parade season. 

This event also offers valuable networking opportunities for subcontractors, suppliers, and industry professionals. Connect directly with Parade builders to discuss potential partnerships, showcase your services, and explore opportunities to collaborate on 2026 Parade homes. Whether you specialize in finishes, landscaping, technology, or trades, this is your chance to get in front of the builders shaping Clark County’s most anticipated home showcase and strengthen your professional network within the BIA community.

 

RSVP 2026 GRO Parade of Homes Builder Kickoff Event - Building Industry Assn. of Clark County <https://members.biaofclarkcounty.org/eventcalendar/Details/2026-gro-parade-of-homes-builder-kickoff-event-1529218?sourceTypeId=Hub>  or With Danielle at danielle@biaofclarkcounty.org

Subject: 2026 GRO Parade of Homes Builder Kickoff Meeting 
When: Wednesday, October 29, 2025 1:00 PM-3:00 PM (UTC-08:00) Pacific Time (US & Canada).
Where: Battle Ground Farmers Market, 15 NE Grace Ave, Battle Ground, WA 98604, USA

 

Hello everyone! Please see the updated address for this event. We will now be meeting at the Battle Ground Farmers Market space. Thank you Max for helping us out with this!

 

Hello! 

 

We would like to invite you to a kickoff for the 2026 show and get us all on the same page early on for an amazing show! Please be sure someone from your company is in attendance if you are not able to be, so that you are informed. Past builders, even if you aren’t building in the 2026 show, we encourage you to come and learn about changes being made.

 

Max Booth and Maddox Pro will be hosting us in their space so that we can grow as needed! Please RSVP with how many can attend from your company, so that we know how much space we need. 

 

Please let me know if you have any questions

 

Danielle
